# wranngle/career_architect — minimal gitignore
#
# This repo is treated as cloud document storage, not a deployable
# package. Everything that's "work product" gets committed and pushed
# so it survives ephemeral Claude Code on the web sessions.
#
# Only THREE categories are excluded:
#   1. Secrets that would be auto-scanned and burned if public
#   2. Regeneratable build artifacts too large to track usefully
#   3. Transient runtime state (locks, pids) that have no value at rest

# 1 — Secrets (DO NOT COMMIT)
# Repo is going public — restored upstream's .env-ignore policy.
# User-data files (cv.md, config/profile.yml, modes/_profile.md,
# article-digest.md, portals.yml, data/applications.md, data/pipeline.md,
# reports/*.md, output/*.pdf, jds/*.md, interview-prep/*) remain tracked
# from the prior cloud-doc-storage policy era. Re-add them here if you
# want them out of new commits — they'll still be in history.
.env
.env.*

# 2 — Regeneratable build artifacts
node_modules/
.next/
out/
build/
dist/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.so
*.egg-info/
*.egg

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
.nyc_output/
coverage/

# 3 — Transient runtime state
batch/.batch-state.lock/
batch/batch-runner.pid
batch/.resolved-prompt-*.md
.resolved-prompt-*
.update-dismissed
.update-lock
*.bak
*.tmp
*.temp
career-dashboard

# 4 — Stale per-day artifacts (regeneratable; don't pollute history)
data/ranked-*.tsv
